description: Commit message format rules for the Lokalaku monorepo. Apply when generating or reviewing git commit messages.
globs:
alwaysApply: false
---

When writing Git commit messages for this repository, always follow the Conventional Commits format defined in `docs/COMMIT_CONVENTION.md`.

Format: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>`

Types: `feat` | `fix` | `docs` | `refactor` | `test` | `chore` | `perf` | `ci` | `revert` | `style`

Valid scopes:
- Apps: `api` `consumer` `merchant` `courier` `wholesale` `backoffice` `website`
- Packages: `domain` `data` `core-auth` `core-network` `ui-kit` `utils`
- Other: `infra` `docs` `workspace`

Rules:
- Imperative mood: "add X" not "added X"
- ≤ 72 characters total on the header line
- No trailing period
- Acronyms (OTP, JWT, POS, PIN, GPS) may stay uppercase within the subject
- Include `Implements: REQ-XX-NNN` footer when a PRD requirement is satisfied
- Include `See: ADR-NNN` footer when an architecture decision is referenced
- Include `Closes: #NNN` footer when a GitHub issue is resolved
- Output only the raw commit message — no markdown fences or commentary
